<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4654968>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 1. Strobopagurus sibogae (De Saint Laurent, 1972). a, shield and cephalic appendages; b, left cheliped; c, right cheliped; d, right 2nd pereopod, lateral; e, merus of same, lateral; f, right 3rd pereopod, lateral; g, merus of same, lateral; h, propodus and dactyl of left 4th pereopod, lateral; i, telson. Scales = 2 mm (a-c), 3 mm (d-g), 0.5 mm (h), and 1 mm (i). (Male [SL 6.0 mm], Western Australia, WAM 1314 -86)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4654968/files/figure.png" .

